node.text:
This July 9, the first storyline of the season kicks off with 
🌳The Haunting of Moss Creek! 👻
.
Join Char, Squirtle, Eevee and some special guests in this 5-part series as they investigate the strange occurrences in the woods, to try and solve the mystery and uncover secrets.
.
I love writing ghost stories, so I’m excited to share this with you all over the coming weeks! It’s gonna be super fun 👻
.
#lilcharandthegang #fanart #fancomic #pokemon #webcomic

node.text:
Invisible
.
As a refresher, Ghost-types in the Lil Char universe are the same as ghosts would be treated in most human fantasy stories; they’re pretty secretive, have their own society with their own rules, most living Pokemon don’t believe in them, etc. So a ghost kid being friends with a living kid is a bit against the rules, which is why they’re trying to stay quiet about it. This will come up later ;)
.
Also don’t swallow electronics.
.
.
#lilcharandthegang #comic #fancomic #webcomic #pokemon #fanart

node.text:
Mooskit evolution line 💧❄️
.
Second of my Canadian Pokémon starters, the water moose Mooskit! Based on a moose with a little beaver flair, this clumsy little water type grows up into a powerhouse Pokemon. 
.
I chose a moose to be the water type because moose are actually really good swimmers and very fond on the water. The line is also inspired by ice sports! Elksko’s antlers are based on skate blades and the ruff/cape are inspired by figure skaters. Reignhart’s head js shaped after a hockey’s goalie helmet and the beaver tail knee pads based on goalie pads!
.
💧
Mooskit is constantly stumbling over it’s own large feet on land, but once in water it can swim and dive with incredible grace.
💧
When an Elksko is upset it’s antlers can turn so cold they burn to the touch.
💧
Reignhart’s knee pads act as a defensive shield and allow it to plow through snow drifts. In heavy storms it is able to carry smaller Pokémon in it’s antlers to safety.
